Here's how to invoke a method with a return value:
```
declare
    strobj = StringObject;
    retval = integer not null;
begin
    retval = strobj.WriteToFile(filename = 'output.txt');
    if retval != ER_OK then
        message 'Error writing file.';
    endif;
end
```
This invokes WriteToFile and assigns the return value to retval.

To use a dynamic method name:
```
declare
    methodName = varchar(32) not null;
    obj = MyClass;
begin
    methodName = 'Calculate';
    obj.:methodName();
end
```
This invokes the method specified by the methodName variable.

Error handling in method invocation:
```
declare
    result = integer not null;
begin
    result = obj.RiskyOperation();
    if result < 0 then
        message 'Error occurred: ' || char(result);
    endif;
end
```
This checks the return value of RiskyOperation for errors.

To invoke a method on a system class:
```
declare
    strObj = StringObject;
    length = integer;
begin
    strObj.Value = 'Hello, World!';
    length = strObj.Length();
end
```
This invokes methods on the StringObject system class.
